The paper deals with problems related to graph theory and logic, which are common topics in computer science. Specifically, it focuses on the compatibility and strict compatibility problems for unrooted phylogenetic trees, which are related to the notions of containing as a minor and containing as a topological minor in the graph community. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
